HEADWORD: Water supply
<hw>Wa"ter sup*ply"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A supply of water;
specifically, water collected, as in reservoirs, and conveyed, as by
pipes, for use in a city, mill, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water tabby</ent>⟦br⟧
